We want the topic selector of ANSWERS-749 to show up at the first usage of Answers 3.0. This means that a user attribute needs to be defined somewhere to determine if user has viewed the Topic Selector before or not. It should cover two scenarios, in pseudocode:

* If "hasViewedTopicSelectorBefore == False": redirect to Topic Selector and set "hasViewedTopicSelectorBefore" to True once they have chosen their tags or when they choose "Please skip this".
* If "hasViewedTopicSelectorBefore == True": don't redirect to the Topic Selector and show the requested page instead.

